	(34,'Mikro-Dismembrator U and S','<p>Laboratory ball mills Mikro-Dismembrator U and Mikro-Dismembrator S are  suited for disintegration and homogenisation of brittle, frozen or hard  materials. Whereas the Mikro-Dismembrator U with its shaking frequency  of 2.000/min is usable for most applications, the new Mikro-Dismembrator  S laboratory ball mill with a maximum frequency of 3.000/min is  especially well suited for fast homogenisation of samples frozen in  liquid nitrogen, for instance biopsy materials taken for diagnostic  purposes. This results in much faster isolation of DNA, RNA or proteins  than with protocols involving manual grinding, thereby reducing the risk  of sample degradation. Reproducibility of the disintegration process is  guaranteed by digital control of shaking frequency and time. A complete  line of shaking flasks and grinding balls is available, including  adaptors for small disposable vessels and microplates.</p>','<table class=\"contenttable\" width=\"277\" height=\"53\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Line voltage</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>230 V</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Line frequency</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>50/60 Hertz</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Wattage</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>120 W</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table class=\"contenttable\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Shaking frequency</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>100 - 2000</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Dimensions (WxDxH)</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>297 x 205 x 259 mm</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Weight</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>19 kg</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Protection type</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>IP20</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Connections</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>Class I cold socket, separate cable approx. 3 m</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Protection class</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>