	(65,'CERTOMAT RM','<div class=\"csc-default\" style=\"display: block;\">\r\n<h3>Description</h3>\r\n<p>Benchtop shaker CERTOMAT<sup>&reg;</sup> RM shows all the features of the CERTOMAT<sup>&reg;</sup> S II with one important technical detail in addition: Adjustable mass  compensation. While all other benchtop shakers have to use a fixed  weight to compensate imbalances caused by the movement of mass, the  CERTOMAT<sup>&reg;</sup> RM has a compensation weight that can be moved  along an axis to the position optimally counteracting imbalance. This  patented feature makes it possible to run even high loads at maximum  speed without increased vibration and running noise. Setting of the  compensation weight is done from the outside of the housing with a  simple tool.</p>\r\n<h3>Obligatory Shaker Accessories</h3>\r\n<p>To make it functional,  every CERTOMAT&reg; shaker or incubation shaker requires a tray. Available  tray sizes are 420 x 420 mm (E/EU) and 800 x 420 mm (F/FU). Suitable  trays, clamps and further accessories are listed with each instrument.</p>\r\n</div>','<table class=\"contenttable\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Interior dimensions (WxDxH)</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>Depending on tray, mounting system and other accessories</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Adjustable mass compensation</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>Yes</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Stacking</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>none</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Heating capacity</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>none</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Cooling capacity</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>none</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Accuracy</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>Max. &plusmn;1 % of final value</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Line voltage</strong></td>\r\n<td>\r\n<div>230 V</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table class=\"contenttable\" width=\"979\" height=\"401\">\r\n<tbody>\r