	(68,'VivaSpec','<p>The VivaSpec LS is a dedicated instrument for Life Science applications. The preprogrammed methods can be used for:<br />&ndash; Nucleic acid quantifi cation and purity control<br />&ndash; Protein assays: Bradford, Lowry, BCA, Biuret, direct UV measurements<br />&ndash; Cell density (OD600)<br />&ndash; Simple absorption measurements</p>\r\n<p>For all these methods the calculation of the results is performed automatically taking dilution factors into consideration.<br />In addition to the Life Science applications the VivaSpec and VivaSpec+ instruments offer the ability to create your own assays which can be stored in password protected folders.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The following testing methods can be applied:<br />&ndash; Measurement of single and multiple wavelengths<br />&ndash; Concentration calculation<br />&ndash; Scan within two user defi ned wavelengths (from 200 nm to 900 nm) with automatic peak detection<br />&ndash; Generation of calibration curves<br />&ndash; Kinetic measurements<br />All versions use a maintanance-free longlife Xenon lamp as light source, a large graphical display and a USB port forconnection to a PC. The required softwareis already included. Optional accessoriesare printer, SD card reader or a Bluetooth&reg; module, all of them available either pre-installed or separately.</p>\r\n<p>For measurements in the microliter range (0.7 &mu;l to 5 &mu;l), the Hellma TrayCell offers a sophisticated solution. Having the identical dimensions of a standard cell it can be inserted in the cuvette holder. During all steps the cell remains<br />in the photometer for reliable results.</p>','<table border=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Wavelength range</strong></td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;190&ndash;1100 nm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Spectral bandwidth</strong></td>\r\n<td>5 nm (3 nm VivaSpec+)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Wavelength accuracy</strong></td>\r\n<td>&plusmn; 2 nm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Wavelength reproducibility </strong></td>\r\n<td>&plusmn; 1 nm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Light source</strong></td>\r\n<td>Xenon lamp</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Beam height</strong></td>\r\n<td>15 mm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>&nbsp;Detector</strong></td>\r\n<td>1024 CCD Array</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Photometric range</strong></td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;&ndash;0.3 to 2.5 A</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Photometric reproducibility</strong></td>\r\n<td>&plusmn; 0.003 A (0 to 0.5 A),<br /> &plusmn; 0.007 A (0.5 &ndash;1.0 A)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Dimensions (W + D + H)</strong></td>\r\n<td>260 + 390 + 100 mm</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Weight </strong></td>\r\n<td>&lt; 4.5 kg</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Power input</strong></td>\r\n<td>90&ndash;250 V, 50|60 Hz</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong><br /><strong></strong> <br /><br /><br /><br /><strong></strong> <br /><strong></strong><br /><strong></strong></p>','SPM_Viva_Spec_Main_Image.jpg'),
	(69,'Medline UV','<p>Spectrophotometer with wavelength ranging from 190nm-1000nm. Available in single beam or dual beam spectrophotometers.</p>','<p><img src=\"/panatrade/uploads/images/medline_spectro_main_image.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"572\" height=\"436\" /></p>','SPM_Medline_Visible_Light_Spectrophotometer_Main_Image.jpg'),
	(70,'Manual Mass Comparator','<p>Manual mass comparators for mass metrology applications, such as the  calibration of mass standards and weights. The monolithic weigh cells  are manufactured as a single structure from a high quality aluminum  alloy and deliver results with outstanding repeatability. Sartorius  manual mass comparators are available with load ranges of 2.2 lbs, 132  lbs and 6,613 lbs. You can order additional draft shields for nearly all  weigh cells.</p>','<p><img src=\"/panatrade/uploads/images/manual_mass_comparator.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"564\" height=\"942\" /></p>','COM_Manual_Mass_Comp.jpg'),
	(71,'Automatic Mass Comparator','<p>Automated weight handling provides the best repeatability. Sartorius mass comparators with a load alternator perform fully automatic mass comparison of individual reference mass standards and groups of weights in any combination. As no additional cylindrical or stackable weights are required, loss of accuracy is prevented.</p>\r\n<p>Relatively large objects, such as disk weights, buoyancy artifacts and pressure disks, can also be easily positioned for determination of their mass. To determine air density, we recommend our climate measurement station YCM02C|YCM03C and YCM05C along with the associated software.</p>\r\n<p><br />The ScalesNet32 software enables all mass and volume comparators, automatic systems and climate measurementstations in a mass laboratory to be networked together. The software is designed for data acquisition, automatic equipment control, data evaluation and storage, and generation of calibration certificates. ScalesNet32 covers all internationalrequirements placed on a professional mass<br />&nbsp;laboratory</p>','<p><img src=\"/panatrade/uploads/images/automatic_mass_comparator.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"761\" height=\"521\" /></p>','COM_Automatic_Mass_Comp.jpg'),
	(72,'Weight ','<p><strong>Weight Sets</strong></p>\r\n<div class=\"description-short\">Individual E1, E2, F1, F2 and M1 OIML class weight sets. The sets  are made of highly polished special steel, nickel silver, galvanised  brass or aluminium. Choose from weight sets including wire weights, leaf  weights or knob weights from 1 g to 50 kg.</div>\r\n<div class=\"description-short\">\r\n<p><strong>Block Shaped Weights</strong></p>\r\n<div class=\"description-short\">Individual block shaped M1 and M2 OIML class weights. The weights  are made of black painted grey cast . You can order the block shapped  weights from 5 kg to 50 kg.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"description-short\">\r\n<p><strong>Cylindrical Weights</strong></p>\r\n<div class=\"description-short\">Individual F1, F2 and M1 OIML class weights. The special steel or  grey cast cylindrical weights are highly polished or painted black,  corrosion-resistant and available from 100 kg to 1000 kg. The  cylindrical weights are non-magnetisable and have a density of 8.0 g/cm<sup>3</sup>.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"description-short\">\r\n<p><strong>Leaf Weights</strong></p>\r\n<div class=\"description-short\">Individual F1 OIML class weights, made of aluminimum or nickel  silver. The aluminum leaf weights are available from 1 mg to 5 mg and  have a density of  2.7 g/cm<sup>3</sup>. The nickel silver leaf weights can be ordered from 10 mg to 500 mg and feature a density of  8.7 g/cm<sup>3</sup>. Packaged in a plastic case the leaf weights are comfortably to store.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"description-short\">\r\n<p><strong>Knob Weights</strong></p>\r\n<div class=\"description-short\">Individual E1, E2, F1, F2 and M1 OIML class weights. The special  steel knob weights are highly polished, corrosion-resistant and  available from 1 g to 50 kg. They are non-magnetisable and have a  density of 8.0 g/cm<sup>3</sup>. Packaged in a plastic case (up to 20 g) or a wooden case (from 50 g) the knob weights are comfortably to store.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"description-short\">\r\n<p><strong>Wire Weights</strong></p>\r\n<div class=\"description-short\">Individual E1 and E2 OIML class weights. The special steel wire  weights are available from 1 mg to 500 mg, are non-magnetisable and have  a density of 8.0 g/cm<sup>3</sup>. Packaged in a plastic case the wire weights are comfortably to store.</div>\r\n</div>','<p><strong>Weight Set</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"/panatrade/uploads/images/weught_set.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Wire Weight/ Leaf Weight</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"/panatrade/uploads/images/wire_weight.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Knob Weight</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"/panatrade/uploads/images/knob_weight.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Rectangular Weight</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"/panatrade/uploads/images/rectangular_weight.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br /></strong></p>',''),
