	(76,'Focus II Monocular Microscope','<div style=\"width: 100%; float: left;\">\r\n<h3>Ideal for laboratory usage in schools and universities.</h3>\r\n<p><br />Monocular microscope supplied with a 10x18 mm eyepiece, a  precentred focusable Abbe NA1.25 condenser and achromatic objectives -  4x, 10x, and 40x. The optical head is inclined at 45&deg; and turns through  360&deg; while the mechanical stage allows for full X-Y movement of the  slide during use.</p>\r\n</div>','<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: large;\">NEW FOCUS 1100.4000</span></strong><br /><strong><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Monocular biological microscope</span></strong><br /><strong>Optical head</strong>: monocular, inclined at 45&deg; and 360&deg; rotatable<br /><strong>Eyepiece</strong>: 10x/18mm wide-field with pointer, mounted student proof<br /><strong>Nosepiece</strong>: triruple, revolving with click stop<br /><strong>Objectives: achromatic</strong><br />- 4x / 0.10 / 160 /-<br />- 10x / 0.25 / 160 / 0.17<br />- 40x / 0.65 / 160 / 0.17 spring loaded<br /><strong>Precondenser including blue filter</strong><br /><strong>Stag</strong>e: X-Y size 120x120mm with fixed iris diaphragm and filter holder. Two stage clamps.<br /><strong>Focusing knobs</strong>: coaxial fine and coarse<br /><strong>Mains power</strong>: 220-240V/50-60Hz (euro connector)<br /><strong>Converter</strong>: built-in low voltage (12V - electronic) with light intensity control<br /><strong>Bulb</strong>: halogen 12V/20W/G4<br /><strong>LED version </strong>: High intensity 5 Watt LED illumination 110v/220v<br /><strong>Supplied with</strong>: 1 spare bulb, 2 spare fuses, dust cover and instruction manual<br /><strong>Packing:</strong> two styrofoam shelves in a cardboard box<br /><strong>Packing dimensions:</strong> 27.5x24.5x42.5cm (WxDxH). Gross weight: 4 kg</p>','CTM_Focus_2_Main_Image.jpg'),
