	(78,'Akropol Microscope for Polarization','<p>The Akropol from CETi is an effective introductory model for educational  applications whereby samples need to be viewed through polarised light.</p>','<p><span style=\"font-size: large;\">CETI AKROPOL</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>STUDENT MICROSCOPE FOR POLARISATION</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Binocular polarising microscope</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Optical head</strong>: 360&ordm; Degree rotatable</p>\r\n<p>- binocular, inclined at 30&deg;</p>\r\n<p>- Interpupillary distance adjustment 53 to 75mm</p>\r\n<p>- dioptric compensation: on one eyepiece tubes</p>\r\n<p><strong>Eyepieces:</strong> high eyepoint 10x/16mm wide-field</p>\r\n<p><strong>Nosepiece:</strong> Quadruple reversed and revolving with click stop</p>\r\n<p><strong>Objectives supplied</strong></p>\r\n<p>- SP 4x / 0.10 / 160 / -</p>\r\n<p>- SP 10x / 0.25 / 160 / 0.17</p>\r\n<p>- SP 40x / 0.65 / 160 / 0.17 (spring loaded)</p>\r\n<p>- SP 100x / 1.25/ 160 / 0.17 (spring loaded)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Polarising set:</strong> polariser and analyser</p>\r\n<p><strong>Precondenser with field diaphragm</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Condenser:</strong></p>\r\n<p>- brightfield Abbe - NA 1.25</p>\r\n<p><strong>Stage:</strong></p>\r\n<p>- round centrable and rotating stage (360&deg;)</p>\r\n<p>- graduated</p>\r\n<p>- diameter: 120mm</p>\r\n<p>- two stage clamps</p>\r\n<p><strong>Focusing knobs:</strong></p>\r\n<p>- coaxial coarse and fine</p>\r\n<p>- tension adjustment ring (on left knob)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Mains power:</strong> 220-240V/50-60 Hz</p>\r\n<p><strong>Converter:</strong> built-in low voltage (6V- electronic) with light intensity control</p>\r\n<p><strong>Bulb:</strong> halogen 6V/20W/G4</p>\r\n<p><strong>Supplied with:</strong> 1 spare bulb, spare fuse, immersion oil 10ml, dust cover</p>\r\n<p><strong>Packing:</strong> two styrofoam shelves in a cardboard box</p>\r\n<p><strong>Packing dimensions:</strong> 48x38x24cm (HxWxD). Gross weight: 7 kg</p>','CTM_Akropol_Main_Im