	(86,'Magtex','<p>Trinocular microscopes witht transmitted and reflected illumination.  Ideal for biological and materials usage for both translucent and opaque  samples.</p>','<p><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong>MAGTEX-T</strong></span><br /><strong>Reflected and Transmitted Light Microscope</strong><br /><strong>Specifications:</strong><br /><strong>Optical head:</strong><br />- trinocular, including vertical photo/video port (&Oslash;30mm) on sliding prism<br />- interpupillary distance adjustment (Siedentopf type): 53 to 75 mm<br />- dioptric compensation: on one eyepiece tube<br /><strong>Eyepieces:</strong> 10x/18mm wide-field<br /><strong>Nosepiece:</strong> quintuple reversed and revolving with click stop<br /><strong>Objectives:</strong> Planachromatic (CCS Optics)<br />- PL LWD 5x / 0.12 / 160 / 0,17<br />- PL LWD 10x / 0.25 / 160 / 0.17<br />- PL LWD 20x / 0.40 / 160 / 0.17 spring loaded<br />- PL LWD 50x / 0.60 / 160 / 0.17 (oil) spring loaded<br />Precondenser with field diaphragm<br /><strong>Condenser:</strong><br />- brightfield Abbe - NA 1.25<br />- iris diaphragm and filter holder<br />- centrable through a centring device<br />- focusable with rack and pinion height adjustment system<br /><strong>Stage:</strong><br />- size 210x140mm with built-in mechanical stage and slide clip<br />- Transversal and longitudinal adjustment by fingertip control<br />- 70mm transversal movement<br />- 50mm longitudinal movement<br />- nonius reading up to 0.1 mm<br /><strong>Focusing knobs:</strong><br />- coaxial coarse and fine<br />- pre-focusing mechanism (on left knob)<br />- tension adjustment ring (on right knob)<br /><strong>Mains power:</strong> 220-240V/50-60 Hz (Euro connector)<br /><strong>Converter:</strong> built-in low voltage (6V- electronic) with light intensity control<br /><strong>Illumination:</strong><br /><strong>Incident Light:</strong> 6V/20W halogen lamp<br /><strong>Transmitted Light:</strong> 6V/20W halogen lamp<br /><strong>Sup