	(88,'Ster Fixed Magnification Stereo Microscope','<p>The Ster series&nbsp;of stereo microscopes are&nbsp;designed for educational  use.&nbsp;They are&nbsp;particularly well suited to viewing specimens at low  magnifications (fixed) with the use of halogen illumination.</p>','<p><br /><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong>Model: STEREO-10P</strong></span><br /><strong>Product ref: 1111.0010</strong><br /><strong>Head type: </strong>Binocular<br /><strong>Interpupillary distance adjustment:</strong> 55 to 75mm<br />Dioptric adjustment on one eyepiece<br /><strong>Eyepieces: </strong>10x/20mm Wide fi eld (incl. rubber eye-cups)<br /><strong>Magnifi cation:</strong> 20x<br /><strong>Stage:</strong> Black / white contrast plate with slide clips</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong>Model: STEREO-30 2.L</strong></span><br /><strong>Product ref: 1111.0030</strong><br /><strong>Head type: </strong>Binocular, inclined at 45&deg; and 360&deg; rotatable<br /><strong>Interpupillary distance adjustment:</strong> 55 to 75mm<br />Dioptric adjustment on one eyepiece<br /><strong>Eyepieces:</strong> 10x/20mm Wide fi eld<br /><strong>Magnifi cation:</strong> 20x and 40x<br /><strong>Illumination:</strong> Episcopic ~ 12V / 10W (fi xed settings)<br />Diascopic ~ 12V / 10W (fi xed settings)<br /><strong>Stage: </strong>Frosted and black / white contrast plate<br /><strong>Mains power:</strong> 220-240V / 50-60Hz</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong></strong></span><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong>Model: TWIN-7 C</strong></span><br /><strong>Product ref: 1111.0007</strong><br /><strong>Head type:</strong> Binocular, inclined at 45&deg; and 360&deg; rotatable<br /><strong>Interpupillary distance adjustment:</strong> 55 to 75mm<br />Dioptric adjustment on one eyepiece<br /><strong>Eyepieces:</strong> 10x/20mm Wide fi eld<br /><strong>Magnifi cation:</strong> 20x and 40x<br /><strong>Illumination: </strong>Episcopic ~ 12V / 10W (fi xed setti