	(89,'Star  Fixed magnification Stereo Microscope','<p>The Star is a stereo microscope designed for educational and  professional use. It is particularly well suited to viewing specimens at  low magnifications and introduces the use of LED lighting into the  stereo range of microscopes.</p>','<p><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong>STAR-LED </strong></span><br /><strong>New Binocular stereomicroscope with LED illumination</strong><br /><strong>Optical head: </strong>Binocular, inclined at 45&deg; 360&deg; rotatable<br />- interpupillary distance adjustment: 50-75mm<br />- dioptric adjustment on one eyepiece<br /><strong>Eyepiece: </strong>10x/20mm Widefield. Anti fungal optics.<br /><strong>Magnification:</strong> 20x and 40x with turret changer- Field of view 10mm / 5mm<br />10x and 30x turrent changer available as special option.<br /><strong>Working range:</strong> 100 mm<br /><strong>Focusing device:</strong><br />- rack and pinion<br />- fixed on vertical column<br /><strong>Illumination:</strong> Variable light intensity<br />- episcopic: fixed under the optical head - High intensity 3W LED<br />- diascopic: built-in the rectangular base - High intensity 3W LED<br />- 2 individual on/off switches<br />- 2 stage clamps<br /><strong>Mains power:</strong> 220-240V/50-60Hz (euro connector)<br /><strong>Supplied with </strong>dust cover, rubber eye cups &amp; manual<br /><strong>Converter: </strong>built-in low voltage (12V-electronic)<br /><strong>Packing dims:</strong> 34x18x35cm (WxDxH). Gross weight: 4,0kg</p>','SSM_Star_Main_Image.jpg'),
	(90,'Twin-7','<p>The&nbsp;Twin series&nbsp;of stereoscopic microscopes are&nbsp;designed for educational  and professional&nbsp;use.&nbsp;They are&nbsp;particularly well suited to viewing  specimens at low magnifications (with variable magnification) with the  use of halogen illumination.</p>','<p><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong>Model: TWIN-Z</strong></span><br /><strong>Product ref: 1111.0003</strong><br /><strong>Head type: </strong>Binocular, inclined at 45&deg; and 360&deg; rotatable<br /><strong>Interpupillary distance adjustment:</strong> 55 to 75mm<br />Dioptric adjustment on one eyepiece<br /><strong>Eyepieces: </strong>10x/20mm Wide fi eld<br /><strong>Zoom Range:</strong> 0.7x to 4.5x<br /><strong>Illumination:</strong> Episcopic ~ 12V / 10W (variable)<br />Diascopic ~ 12V / 10W (variable)<br /><strong>Stage:</strong> Frosted and black / white contrast plate<br /><strong>Mains power:</strong> 220-240V / 50-60Hz</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong>Model: TWIN-7 C</strong></span><br /><strong>Product ref: 1111.0007</strong><br /><strong>Head type:</strong> Binocular, inclined at 45&deg; and 360&deg; rotatable<br /><strong>Interpupillary distance adjustment: </strong>55 to 75mm<br />Dioptric adjustment on one eyepiece<br /><strong>Eyepieces:</strong> 10x/20mm Wide fi eld<br /><strong>Magnifi cation:</strong> 20x and 40x<br /><strong>Illumination: </strong>Episcopic ~ 12V / 10W (fi xed settings)<br />Diascopic ~ 12V / 10W (fi xed settings)<br /><strong>Stage: </strong>Frosted and black / white contrast plate<br /><strong>Mains power:</strong> 220-240V / 50-60Hz</p>','SSM_Twin7_Main_Image.jpg'),
	(91,'Varizoom Stereoscpoic Microscope','<p>Supplied in binocular configuration with the option for the addition of a  beam splitter arm to allow for attachment of a digital or video camera.  The choice of zoom ratios ensures that the correct model can be  selected for the required application supplied with&nbsp; 10x / 22mm  super-field eyepieces as standard, both with dioptric compensation.  Additional eyepieces and corrective planachromatic lenses allow for a  total magnification range of&nbsp;4x&nbsp;up to&nbsp;320x (model dependant). The  variable incident and transmitted LED light sources&nbsp;ensures that there  is&nbsp;no heating of the sample when viewing live samples. The microscope  comes complete with a frosted glass stage to allow use of both LED light  sources.</p>','<p><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong>VARIZOOM 7700.0000</strong></span><br /><strong>Binocular stereoscopic binocular zoom microscope</strong><br /><strong>Parallel Optical Zoom system</strong><br /><strong>Infinity optics </strong>- Available in three different zoom ratio<br /><strong>Optical head: </strong>Binocular, inclined at 20&deg;<br />- interpupillary distance adjustment : 45 to 75 mm<br />- dioptric compensation on both eyepiece tubes<br /><strong>Eyepieces </strong>10x/22mm super wide-field<br /><strong>Magnification-</strong> zoom system - bilateral knobs three different zoom range<br />1:6 zoom ratio standard magnification 8x to 50x magnification<br />1 :8 zoom ratio standard magnification 8x to 64x<br />1 :10 zoom ratio standard magnification 8x to 80x<br /><strong>Focusing mount</strong>: rack and pinion system.<br /><strong>Standard working distance: </strong>78 mm Focusing range 105mm<br /><strong>Objectives: </strong>planachromatic 1x supplied as standard<br /><strong>Illumination:</strong><br />- episcopic: fixed under the optical head and directional condensing lens LED 5W<br />- diascopic: built into base LED 5W<br /><strong>Stage :</strong> - frosted and black/