	(92,'Light Source for Stereoscopic Microscope','<div style=\"width: 100%; float: left;\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For photomicrography&nbsp;applications  Ceti&nbsp;recommends the use of an external light source. Either a cold light  source or an LED ring illuminator provides high intensity illumination  for use with stereo microscopes, ideal for capturing excellent shots  without heating the sample.</p>\r\n</div>','<p><strong></strong><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong>Cold Light Source 150 watt</strong></span><br /><strong>Fiber optic illuminator</strong><br /><strong>Main power: </strong>220V AC 50 Hz (euro connector))<br /><strong>Light intensity: </strong>regulation with electronic control 0-100%<br /><strong>Color temperature: </strong>3200&deg;K<br /><strong>Heat filter</strong><br /><strong>Bulb: </strong>21V 150W halogen reflector bulb (500 burning hours)<br /><strong>Cooling system: </strong>axial ventilator<br /><strong>Packing dimensions</strong>: 38x26x21 cm ((WxDxH). Gross Weight: 3,6 Kg<br /><strong>Spare Parts for Cold light source</strong><br />7060.2101 Bulb halogen reflector 21V 150W</p>','ACS_LightSOurce_Main_Image.jpg'),
