	(212,'Optifit Pipette Tips','<p>n liquid handling, the pipette and the tip always form a system.  Perfect tip fitting and sealing to the pipette secures the best possible  accuracy and precision. Thus Biohit\'s precision-made Optifit Pipette  Tips, filtered and non-filtered, are made to provide excellent  reproducibility and accuracy. They fit perfectly with Biohit pipettes  and are suitable for use with most other pipette brands.<br /><br />As the  tip is an integral component of the pipetting system, its shape,  material properties, fit and purity have a considerable influence on  pipetting results. Therefore all our products are tested and certified  according to strict quality standards. Biohit Tips are manufactured in a  protected ISO 8 Clean Room environment for maximal purity, following  Good Manufacturing Practices (GMP) and causing as little environmental  loading as possible. All Biohit Tips are fully traceable.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Perfect fitting and sealing with Biohit pipettes secures the best possible accuracy and precision </li>\r\n<li>Compatible with most other pipette makes </li>\r\n<li>Strict quality standards, ISO 9001 and ISO 13485, followed from R&amp;D to production and delivery </li>\r\n<li>CE/IVD certified </li>\r\n<li>ISO 8 Clean Room manufacturing process </li>\r\n<li>The highest quality virgin polypropylene used as raw material</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Material used in tips, trays and racks (polypropylene) is 100% recyclable</li>\r\n<li>Fully autoclavable (121&ordm;, 20 min) racks can be reused with Refill Tips</li>\r\n<li>Air-tight plastic wrapping for maximal purity - wrapping is regular waste</li>\r\n<li>Flip-top boxes can be easily opened and closed using a single hand</li>\r\n<li>Colour coding of the tip trays allows for easy matching with a suitable Biohit pipette</li>\r\n<li>RNase, DNase and endotoxin free certified by lot number.</li>\r\n<li>Also available as e-beam pre-sterilized</li>\r\n<li>Filter Tips available as pre-sterilized only (non-autoclavable)</li>\r\n<li>New rack labels indicate tip volume, tip type, lot number, etc.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n</ul>','<p>These non-filtered Optifit Tips are available in various packaging and purity options for all your needs:<br /><br /></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Single Tray racks for safer laboratory work</span><br /><br />- For all tip models from 10 &micro;l to 5000 &micro;l<br />- DNase, RNase and endotoxin free certified by Lot. Number</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Eco Refill System</span><br /><br />- Refill Towers - ecological and space-saving<br />- Refill Packs - ecological and purity certified<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Bulk Package - the economical option</span></li>\r\n</ol>','PPT_Optifit_Pipette_Tip_Main_Image.jpg'),
	(213,'SafetySpace Filter Tip','<p>Biohit&rsquo;s SafetySpace Filter Tips are made of virgin polypropylene and  they feature filter (PE) barriers to prevent aerosol and liquid  contamination. This helps protect against the risk of  cross-contamination and reduces maintenance requirements of the  pipette.&nbsp; <br /><br />The filter tips are well suited for molecular biology, microbiology, cell culture ad radioactive work. <br /><br />SafetySpace  Filter Tips have more space between the sample and the filter than  conventional filter tips. With SafetySpace Filter Tips you do not need  to worry about the sample touching the filter whatever pipetting  technique or type of liquid you&rsquo;re using.<br /><br /><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">They are particulary useful in</span>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>pipetting foaming liquids like buffers and proteins</li>\r\n<li>pipetting solvents</li>\r\n<li>reverse pipetting</li>\r\n<li>multiple dispensing functions of electronic pipettes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br />The tips are packed in colour-coded single tray racks. They are  certified DNase, RNase and endotoxin free and are e-beam pre-sterilized.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reduce the risk of contamination of the pipette or samples</li>\r\n<li>Made of virgin polypropylene (tip) and polyethylene (filter) </li>\r\n<li>Packed in colour-coded single tray packages, wrapped in air-tight plastic </li>\r\n<li>Certified as DNase, RNase and endotoxin free by lot number</li>\r\n<li>Electron beam pre-sterilized (red dot) </li>\r\n<li>Non autoclavable </li>\r\n<li>CE/IVD certified </li>\r\n<li>Manufactured according to ISO 9001, ISO 14001 &amp; ISO 13485 </li>\r\n<li>Manufactured in ISO 8 Clean Room conditions</li>\r\n</ul>','<table class=\"ordering\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"font-weight: bold;\">\r\n<td>ID<br /></td>\r\n<td>Volume</td>\r\n<td>Item</td>\r\n<td>Package<br /></td>\r\n<td>Quantity</td>\r\n<td>Purity Level<br /></t