33 for 5 and 10 ml Proline Prospenser<br /> Cat No. 721634 for 25 and 50 ml Proline Prospenser</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 721633, 721634</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Adapters for Biohit Dispenser Tip 25 and 50 ml</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 792036</p>\r\n<p><strong>Quantity:</strong> 3</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; <br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Cooling Rack</strong></p>\r\n<p>Thermo-conductive cooling rack for 1,5 ml and 2,0 ml conical and cylindrical microcentrifuge tubes.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 723102</p>','','PAC_Other_Accessories_Main_Image.jpg'),
	(226,'Pipetting Academy','<p><strong>Pipetting Academy help you achieve better results and more comfortable working postures</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>How often do you consider the pain      of pipetting may be related to the instrument or techniques you use when      working in the lab? </li>\r\n<li>Have you considered new or updated      instruments to improve your pipetting experience or work?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Pipetting Academy - a new training program that will help you improve health and safety&nbsp;in the lab </strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Be guided through the essentials      of laboratory ergonomics. </li>\r\n<li>Gain a better understanding of the      ergonomic risks in the laboratory environment and pipetting in      particular.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Perform better without      compromising your health and safety. </li>\r\n<li>Use your tools in a more efficient      way and improve health, safety and performance in the lab.</li>\r\n<li>Be able to instruct your employees      on how to avoid strain injuries and make work more enjoyable.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>In addition to the Pipetting Academy training seminars, a wide range of videos and presentation helps you understand the essential issues in ergonomics, the most important in pipetting techniques and all you should know about calibration and ISO 8655 standards!</p>','','PAY_Pipetting_academy_Main_Image.jpg'),
	(227,'Replacement Battery','<h2><strong>eLINE Replacement Battery</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 731009</p>\r\n<p><strong>Compatible for:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.biohit.com/Liquid%20Handling/pipettes-electronic/products/9/eline-electronic-pipette\">eLINE Electronic Pipette</a></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; <br /></strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2><strong>Proline Replacement Battery</strong></h2>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 711002</p>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<h2><strong>ePET Replacement Battery</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 711002</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>','','PAC_Replacement_Battery_Main_Image.jpg'),
	(228,'Refill Tip Box','<h1><strong>Refill Tip Box</strong></h1>\r\n<h2><strong>Empty Tip Box for Refill System </strong></h2>\r\n<p>DNase, RNase and endotoxin free certified and pre-sterilized Single Refill Packs are particularly suitable for use in laminar hoods or clean rooms, where transferring the tips to the racks is safer. <br /> <br /> Tip Type 10, 300, 350 &micro;l (non-filtered), tip ID A, C, D</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 790910</p>\r\n<p><strong>Quantity:</strong> 10</p>\r\n<p><strong>Compatible for:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.biohit.com/Liquid%20Handling/pipette-tips/products/38/optifit-tip-non-filtered\">Optifit Tip, Non-Filtered</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<h2><strong>Empty Tip Box for Refill System </strong></h2>\r\n<p>DNase, RNase and endotoxin free certified and pre-sterilized Single Refill Packs are particularly suitable for use in laminar hoods or clean rooms, where transferring the tips to the racks is safer.<br /> <br /> Tip Type 1000, 1200 &micro;l (non-filtered). Tip E, H</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 790920</p>\r\n<p><strong>Quantity:</strong> 10</p>\r\n<p><strong>Compatible for:</strong> <a href=\"http://www.biohit.com/Liquid%20Handling/pipette-tips/products/38/optifit-tip-non-filtered\">Optifit Tip, Non-Filtered</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>','','PAC_Refill_Tip_Box_Main_Image.jpg'),
	(229,'Safe Cone Filters','<h2><strong>Protect your pipette and your sample from contamination</strong></h2>\r\n<p>These unique and replaceable polyethylene (PE) filters act as a final barrier to prevent any fluids and liquid vapours from reaching the internal components of the pipette.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Protect the pipette and sample      from contamination</li>\r\n<li>Prolong the pipette&rsquo;s lifetime</li>\r\n<li>Reduce maintenance intervals</li>\r\n<li>Cost-effective</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Standard Filter</strong><br /> For general applications. Can be used in same type of work as the Plus filter is recommended for, but needs to be changed more frequently.<br /> <br /> <strong>Plus Filter</strong><br /> For more demanding applications such as radioactive work, cell culture, bacterial and virological work and molecular biology.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','<h2><strong>Available Filter Sizes</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Safe-Cone Filter, Standard &oslash; 2.51 mm PE</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cat. number: 721008</p>\r\n<p>Quantity: 50</p>\r\n<p>Compatible for: eLINE Electronic Pipette, mLINE Mechanical Pipette, Proline Mechanical Pipette, Proline Plus Mechanical Pipette</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Safe-Cone Filter, Standard &oslash; 3.15 mm PE</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cat. number: 721007</p>\r\n<p>Quantity: 50</p>\r\n<p>Compatible for: eLINE Electronic Pipette, mLINE Mechanical Pipette, Proline Mechanical Pipette, Proline Plus Mechanical Pipette</p>\r\n<p><strong>Safe-Cone Filter, Standard &oslash; 5.33 mm PE</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cat. number: 721006</p>\r\n<p>Quantity: 50</p>\r\n<p>Compatible for: eLINE Electronic Pipette, mLINE Mechanical Pipette, Proline Mechanical Pipette, Proline Plus Mechanical Pipette</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Safe-Cone Filter, Standard &oslash; 6.73 mm PE</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cat. number: 721005</p>\r\n<p>Quantity: 50</p>\r\n<p>Compatible for: mLINE Mechanical Pipette, Proline Mechanical Pipette, Proline Plus Mechanical Pipette</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Safe-Cone Filter, Standard &oslash; 1.83 mm PE</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cat. number: 721014</p>\r\n<p>Quantity: 50</p>\r\n<p>Compatible for: eLINE Electronic Pipette, mLINE Mechanical Pipette, Proline Mechanical Pipette, Proline Plus Mechanical Pipette</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Safe-Cone Filter, Plus &oslash; 2.51 mm PE</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cat. number: 721018</p>\r\n<p>Quantity: 50</p>\r\n<p>Compatible for: eLINE Electronic Pipette, mLINE Mechanical Pipette, Proline Mechanical Pipette, Proline Plus Mechanical Pipette</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Safe-Cone Filter, Plus &oslash; 3.15 mm PE</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cat. number: 721017</p>\r\n<p>Quantity: 50</p>\r\n<p>Compatible for: eLINE Electronic Pipette, mLINE Mechanical Pipette, Proline Mechanical Pipette, Proline Plus Mechanical Pipette</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Safe-Cone Filter, Plus &oslash; 5.33 mm PE</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cat. number: 721016</p>\r\n<p>Quantity: 50</p>\r\n<p>Compatible for: eLINE Electronic Pipette, mLINE Mechanical Pipette, Proline Mechanical Pipette, Proline Plus Mechanical Pipette</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; <br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Safe-Cone Filter, Plus &oslash; 6.73 mm PE</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cat. number: 721015</p>\r\n<p>Quantity: 50</p>\r\n<p>Compatible for: mLINE Mechanical Pipette, Proline Mechanical Pipette, Proline Plus Mechanical Pipette</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','PAC_Safe_Cone_Filters_Main_Image.jpg'),
	(230,'Pipette Stands','<h2><strong>Stands for mechanical and electronic pipettes</strong></h2>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>When the pipette is not in use, it should be stored in an upright position in order to avoid contamination from dirty benches. Biohit offers stands for all of its pipettes.<br /> <br /> The stylish Biohit Linear Stand is designed for all Biohit mechanical and electronic pipettes, and especially for mLINE, Proline Plus, Proline mechanical and ePET electronic pipettes. The stand is also compatible with a wide range of other pipette brands. <br /> <br /> The compact Carousel Stands are available for all Biohit pipette models, for storage and for charging.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>','<p><strong>Carousel Stand for 6 mechanical pipettes </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 725600</p>\r\n<p><strong>Compatible for:</strong> mLINE Mechanical Pipette, Proline Mechanical Pipette, Proline Plus Mechanical Pipette</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; <br /></strong></p>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<p><strong>Pipette Holder for one pipette</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 725610</p>\r\n<p><strong>Compatible for:</strong> mLINE Mechanical Pipette, Proline Plus Mechanical Pipette</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>Linear Stand for all Biohit pipettes</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 725620</p>\r\n<p><strong>Compatible for:</strong> eLINE Electronic Pipette, mLINE Mechanical Pipette, Proline Mechanical Pipette, Proline Plus Mechanical Pipette</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;eLINE Charging Stand for one pipette</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 730981</p>\r\n<p><strong>Compatible for:</strong> eLINE Electronic Pipette, eLINE Lite Dispenser, eLINE Pro Dispenser</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;eLINE Charging Carousel for 4 pipettes</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 730991</p>\r\n<p><strong>Compatible for:</strong> eLINE Electronic Pipette, eLINE Lite Dispenser, eLINE Pro Dispenser</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp; <br /></strong></p>\r\n<div></div>\r\n<p><strong>Proline Charging Stand for one pipette </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 510001</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Proline Charging Carousel for 4 pipettes</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 511601</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;<br /></strong></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;ePET Stand for one pipette</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 710999</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Proline Pipette Holder for one pipette</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 725610</p>\r\n<p><strong>Compatible for:</strong> Proline Mechanical Pipette</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>','PAC_Pipette_Stands_Main_Image.jpg'),
	(231,'Decontamination','<p>Biohit Proline Biocontrol is ready for use decontamination solution for laboratory equipment such as pipettes, centrifuges, CO2 incubators, and surfaces.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Non-toxic and non-irritating to      humans and animals </li>\r\n<li>Lethal to a broad spectrum of      viruses, bacteria and fungi </li>\r\n<li>Non-corrosive to metals </li>\r\n<li>Odourless and non-staining</li>\r\n<li>Free from alcohol, aldehyde,      phenol and chlorine</li>\r\n<li>Environmentally friendly      (biodegradable) </li>\r\n<li>BS 6471 approved </li>\r\n<li>Non-fuming </li>\r\n<li>Non-mutagenic </li>\r\n<li>Effective for removing odours </li>\r\n<li>Stable for long periods</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Effective Against</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Viruses</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Hepatitis A, B, C, D and E, HIV, Parvovirus, Newcastle Disease</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Bacteria</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Pseudomonas sp., Escherichia coli, Staph. aureus, Proteus mirabilis, Proteus vulgaris, Streptococcus sp., Bacillus sp., Salmonellae, Klebsiella sp., Enterobacter sp., Serratia sp., Mycobacterium sp., Listeria sp. Legionella pneumophilia </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Fungi</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Niger, Penicillium sp., T. mentagrophytes, Candida albicans</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>','','PAC_Decontamination_Main_Image.jpg'),
	(232,'Elbow Pad','<p><strong>Elbow Pad</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pipetting is sometimes heavy work. Hand and shoulders get tired easily in long pipetting series.Improve your working posture with Biohit Elbow Pad. The Elbow Pad is a solution to a more relaxed and ergonomic work. The visco elastic material of the pad relieves contact stress, pain and discomfort during pipetting. The pad is ideal e.g. for</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Long pipetting series</li>\r\n<li>Work requiring high concentration,      e.g. micro plate work or micro volume pipetting</li>\r\n<li>Pipetting work in a laminar hood</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Features and benefits:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Improves pipetting ergonomy</li>\r\n<li>Fits all sizes of elbows</li>\r\n<li>The compact size takes up little      desk space</li>\r\n<li>Made of visco elastic material &ndash;      forms according to body shape</li>\r\n<li>Easily cleaned with ethanol (70 %)      or Biohit Biocontrol decontamination solution</li>\r\n<li>Non-autoclavable</li>\r\n<li>Only available from Biohit</li>\r\n</ul>','','PAC_Elbow_Pad_Main_Image.jpg'),
	(233,'Ergomate','<p>Biohit Ergomate removes the need to hold the plate at any angle and allows safe dispensing, resulting easier, safer and more precise pipetting.</p>\r\n<p>According to ISO 8655 recommendations, dispensing especially small volumes should be done against the inside wall of receiving vessel. Ergomate is an ideal tool for finding proper positioning in pipetting.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Microplate grids for quick      identification and sample management. </li>\r\n<li>Grids are double sided. Reverse      side featuring numbering from 1-12. </li>\r\n<li>When reserved plate holder creates      an ideal aerosol&nbsp;barrier for use in hoods or on bench top surfaces. </li>\r\n<li>Plate holder can be reversed and      used for&nbsp;flat surface pipetting or as an incubation station with lid. </li>\r\n<li>Ideal for safe transporting of      plates.</li>\r\n<li>Non autoclavable</li>\r\n</ul>','<div>\r\n<h2><strong>Available Types</strong></h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><strong>Ergomate Starter Kit</strong></p>\r\n<p>Ergomate Starter Kit, incl. 1 Ergomate Plate holder, grid</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 723105</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Ergomate Microplate Grids</strong></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Double-sided Microplate Grids help you for quicker identification and sample management.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 723101</p>\r\n<p><strong>Quantity:</strong> 10</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>','PAC_Ergomate.jpg'),
	(234,'Reagent Vessel','<div>\r\n<p>Biohit Reagent Vessels for use especially with all multichannel pipettes. Chemically resistant Vessels are made of polypropylene for cost-effective reuse and autoclavability.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>','<p><strong>Reagent Vessel, V-shaped, 120 ml</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Cat. number:</strong> 783500</p>\r\n<p><strong>Quantity:</strong> 16</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>','PAC_Reagent_Vessel_Main_Image.jpg'),
	(235,'Analytical Balance Secura','<p><strong>Easy, Reliable Weighing in Regulated Areas</strong></p>\r\n<p>Secura<sup>&reg;</sup> laboratory balances set new standards for reliability in weighing! Secura<sup>&reg;</sup> balances are designed for customers who work in regulated environments  and need high-quality results without any risk! With Secura<sup>&reg;</sup>, you can now enjoy the security and serenity of knowing that you have done everything right. Based on best practices, Secura<sup>&reg;</sup> ensures the quality of your measurement results, compliance with regulatory requirements and your efficiency as well.</p>\r\n<h3>What\'s included:</h3>\r\n<p>Universal power adapter, in-use cover,  application guide, dust cover for analytical balances and a draft ring  for 0.1 mg balances.</p>\r\n<h3>APC functions:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Weighing without risk &ndash; data transfer to a printer or a computer is blocked when most common operating errors occur</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Total  confidence in your results: Incorrect results from an unleveled balance  are impossible &ndash; thanks to LevelControl, the optoelectronic level  monitoring, alarm messaging and interactive user support feature</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Active monitoring of the USP minimum sample weight requirement &ndash; due to programmed SQmin in the balance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Complete  protection against incorrect results due to an uncalibrated balance &ndash;  thanks to isoCAL, the internal fully automatic calibration and  adjustment function with configurable action level</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Traceable documentation of all calibration and adjustment data inside the balance &ndash; as a result of Cal Audit Trail</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>GLP-compliant printouts with proper time and date stamps &ndash; because of GLP printouts with a Sartorius GLP printer YDP30</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unauthorised changes of weighing settings are not possible &ndash; thanks to password protection</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Easy cleaning for thorough results &ndash; based on an innovative housing design</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Designed for working in laminar air flow environments &ndash; on account of an optimized draft ring and LevelControl</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n</ul>','<p><img src=\"/panatrade/uploads/images/analytical_balance_secura.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"518\" height=\"460\" /></p>','Analytical_Balance_Secura_Main_Image.jpg'),
	(236,'Natural Convection Oven (DETS)','<p><span>Over-temperature limiter and Leakage Breaker</span><br /><span>Digital Timer - 1 min. to 99hr 59min, Delayed On/Off</span><br /><span>Digital LED Display (1&#8451; Resolution) with touch keypads</span><br /><span>Rounded inner chamber corners for easy cleaning and better airflowing</span></p>\r\n<p><span>- Temperature Max. 300&#8451;</span><br /><span>- Programmable controller with RS-485 / RS-232C PC Interface for Monitoring and Data Recording</span></p>','<p><img src=\"/panatrade/uploads/images/screen_shot_2013-11-14_at_5.06.27_pm.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" /></p>','pro01_img08.jpg');
